  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I was booking ticket from IRCTC but due to technical problem, I fail to book the tckt, bt amt got debited from account. By when would that b refunded?",
  "response": "If your payment was debited but the ticket booking failed on IRCTC, the amount is usually refunded automatically within **3 to 7 working days**. However, the refund process can sometimes take up to **10-15 working days**, depending on your bank. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n1. **Check IRCTC Transaction History**:  \n   Log in to your IRCTC account and check the \"Transaction History\" or \"Booked Tickets\" section to confirm if the ticket was not booked.\n\n2. **Wait for Automatic Refund**:  \n   Most refunds are processed automatically. If the ticket booking failed, IRCTC initiates the refund, and your bank processes it.\n\n3. **Contact IRCTC Customer Care**:  \n   If the refund is not credited within 7 working days, contact IRCTC customer care at **0120-4141744** or email them at **care@irctc.co.in**. Provide your transaction details for assistance.\n\n4. **Check with Your Bank**:  \n   If IRCTC confirms the refund but the amount is not credited, contact your bank\u2019s customer care for further details.\n\n   **Note**:  \n   - Refunds are credited to the same account/mode of payment used during the transaction.  \n   - Ensure your bank account or card details are correct in your IRCTC profile.  \n\nIf there\u2019s no resolution, you can also file a grievance with IRCTC through their grievance portal: [https://pgportal.gov.in](https://pgportal.gov.in).",
  "temperature": 1.0,
